definitions.definition: A turning or sliding piece which imparts motion to a rod , lever or block brought into sliding or rolling contact with it.

subdefinitions.definition: A curved wedge, movable about an axis, used for forcing or clamping two pieces together.

definitions.definition: ( UK , dialect ) A ridge or mound of earth.
( climbing ) A spring-loaded camming device , a spring-loaded device for effecting a temporary belay in a rock crevice .
